[5] Selected media reports of transmission outside of mainland China
A. Japanese cruise ship: 99 new cases
Date: Sun 16 Feb 2020 03:53 PM IST
Source: The Economic Times [edited]
https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/world-news/99-more-coronavirus-cases-on-japan-cruise-ship-report/articleshow/74174126.cms


An additional 99 people have tested positive for coronavirus on a cruise ship off the Japan coast, Japanese media said [Mon 17 Feb 2020], citing new figures from the health ministry. That would take the total number of positive cases on the Diamond Princess to 454. It was also not clear whether the figures included 14 US citizens who tested positive for the virus but were allowed to board evacuation flights home.

The Diamond Princess vessel moored in Yokohama near Tokyo has become the 2nd-largest cluster of coronavirus cases outside the epicentre in China. Passengers have been largely confined to quarters since [5 Feb 2020] with only brief and occasional breaks to take air on deck -- with face masks. The quarantine period is over on [Wed 19 Feb 2020] but many countries have decided to repatriate their citizens after an alarming climb in cases on board. The US was the 1st country to evacuate its citizens from the ship but Australia, Canada, Italy, and Hong Kong have indicated they will follow suit.

On land, cases in Japan have risen to 65, with authorities warning that the outbreak is entering a "new phase" and advising people to avoid large gatherings. A public celebration of the new emperor's birthday on [Sun 23 Feb 2020] has been scrapped and organisers of the Tokyo Marathon scheduled on [1 Mar 2020] are reportedly considering cancelling the amateur part of the race.

--
