C. South Korea (Daegu): local transmission
Date: Mon 18 Feb 2020 11:10 KST
Source: Joins news [in Korean, machine trans., edited]
https://news.joins.com/article/23708745


The 31st patient with new coronavirus infection ([COVID-19]) emerged. The Centers for Disease Control and Public Affairs revealed the fact on [18 Feb 2020]. The patient is a 61-year-old woman living in Daegu, with no history off traveling abroad. This is the 1st time a patient has been diagnosed in Daegu, the 1st confirmation of Yeongnam region. The case, who was classified as suspected on [18 Feb 2020], was found to be positive on the virus test."

She visited an Oriental medicine hospital after suffering cold and body aches, and was finally confirmed by of having [COVID-19] at the Daegu Suseong-gu Public Health Center. She is presently isolated and being treated at the Daegu Medical Center, a nationally designated isolation hospital.

[Byline: Kim Yoon-ho, Kim Jung-seok]

